  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Released 05/16/2017 11:22 CT (16:22 UTC)</p><h2 id=\"id-1.12.8-TicketLabels\">Ticket Labels</h2><p>The diagnostic notes section on ticket labels was printing with too much whitespace for line breaks. This has been resolved.</p><p>In addition, for automated prints, a small gray line appeared at the bottom of printed labels; the small gray line has been removed.</p><h2 id=\"id-1.12.8-SuccessMessageStyling\">Success Message Styling</h2><p>The color for success messages has been\u00a0changed to be less... glaring. The new color is as pictured below:</p><h2 id=\"id-1.12.8-PAXdevicepaymentprocessing-recoveringfromnetworkconnectionfailures\">PAX device payment processing - recovering from network connection failures</h2><p>If your network connection fails between the PAX\u00a0device and the RepairQ terminal <em>while</em> processing a payment,\u00a0RepairQ may not receive the payment details from the device. In this scenario you could have a payment processed that RepairQ does not receive, and therefore is unable to\u00a0save\u00a0on the ticket.</p><p>With\u00a0this update we added a new process\u00a0that\u00a0automatically recovers from intermittent connection failures. When a network connection failure occurs, RepairQ\u00a0will still fetch\u00a0the processed payment and save it on the ticket (provided network connection is re-established while you are still working with the ticket).</p>",
      "representation": "export_view",
